import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['x'], bins='auto')
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    name_counts = data['name'].value_counts()
    name_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of name?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
